title: Lunary Archetypes

title: The Alchemist
summary: The Alchemist archetype represents the power to transmute base experiences into gold, finding meaning and growth in all circumstances.

title: The Catalyst
summary: The Catalyst archetype embodies the power to initiate profound change, challenging stagnation and awakening dormant potential.

title: The Empath
summary: The Empath archetype represents profound emotional sensitivity and the gift of deeply feeling and understanding others' experiences.

title: The Grounded One
summary: The Grounded One archetype represents stability, practical wisdom, and the capacity to create secure foundations in uncertain times.

title: The Heart Opener
summary: The Heart Opener archetype represents the courage to love fully, embracing vulnerability as the path to authentic connection.

title: The Lunar Weaver
summary: The Lunar Weaver archetype represents attunement to natural rhythms and cycles, weaving together the threads of intuition and timing.

title: The Mystic
summary: The Mystic archetype represents the direct experience of the divine and the capacity to perceive sacred dimensions of reality.

title: The Protector
summary: The Protector archetype represents the fierce capacity to create safety, defend what is precious, and maintain healthy boundaries.

title: The Restorer
summary: The Restorer archetype embodies the profound capacity for healing and emotional reconstruction, rebuilding foundations that support future growth.

title: The Seeker
summary: The Seeker archetype represents the eternal quest for meaning, driven by an unquenchable thirst for understanding and deeper truth.

title: The Shadow Dancer
summary: The Shadow Dancer archetype represents mastery of the unconscious, transforming darkness into wisdom through integration.

title: The Visionary
summary: The Visionary archetype perceives possibilities that others cannot see, holding space for what could be and inspiring collective evolution.

title: Air Signs
summary: Gemini, Libra, and Aquarius.

title: Angular House
summary: The 1st, 4th, 7th, and 10th houses—the most powerful positions in the chart.

title: Applying Aspect
summary: When a faster planet is moving toward exact aspect with a slower planet.

title: Arabic Parts
summary: Sensitive points calculated from three chart factors (usually Ascendant + Planet A - Planet B).

title: Ascendant
summary: The zodiac sign rising on the eastern horizon at birth, representing your outward personality and how others perceive you.

title: Aspect
summary: An angular relationship between two planets describing how their energies interact.

title: Asteroid
summary: Minor celestial bodies used in astrology for additional nuance.

title: Benefic Planets
summary: Venus and Jupiter - planets considered fortunate and helpful.

title: Birth Chart
summary: Synonymous with natal chart. A celestial snapshot of the sky at your birth.

title: Black Moon Lilith
summary: The lunar apogee representing raw feminine power, shadow, and what we suppress.

title: Cadent House
summary: The 3rd, 6th, 9th, and 12th houses.

title: Cardinal Signs
summary: Signs that begin each season - initiators, leaders, and action-oriented.

title: Cazimi
summary: When a planet is within 17 minutes of arc of the Sun's exact degree.

title: Chiron
summary: The "Wounded Healer" showing your deepest wound and potential for healing others.

title: Combust
summary: When a planet is within 8 degrees of the Sun but not cazimi.

title: Composite Chart
summary: A single chart created from the midpoints of two people's charts.

title: Conjunction
summary: An aspect where two planets are at the same degree, fusing their energies together intensely.

title: Cusp
summary: The boundary between two signs or houses.

title: Decan
summary: Each zodiac sign divided into three 10-degree segments with sub-rulers.

title: Descendant
summary: The point directly opposite the Ascendant, marking the cusp of the 7th house.

title: Detriment
summary: A planet in the sign opposite its domicile, requiring extra effort.

title: Direct
summary: Normal forward motion of a planet through the zodiac.

title: Domicile
summary: A planet in the sign it rules, expressing most naturally and powerfully.

title: Earth Signs
summary: Taurus, Virgo, and Capricorn.

title: Eclipse
summary: Powerful lunations near the lunar nodes bringing significant beginnings or endings.

title: Electional Astrology
summary: The practice of choosing optimal times for important events like weddings, business launches, or surgeries based on favorable planetary alignments.

title: Electional Astrology
summary: The practice of choosing optimal times to begin important activities—weddings, businesses, surgeries—based on astrological timing.

title: Element
summary: The four elements (Fire, Earth, Air, Water) categorizing zodiac signs by temperament.

title: Essential Dignity
summary: A system measuring planetary strength based on sign placement: domicile, exaltation, triplicity, term, and face.

title: Exaltation
summary: A sign where a planet is honored and expresses its highest potential.

title: Fall
summary: A planet in the sign opposite its exaltation, considered its weakest placement.

title: Fire Signs
summary: Aries, Leo, and Sagittarius.

title: Fixed Signs
summary: Signs in the middle of each season - stabilizers, persistent, and determined.

title: Generational Planets
summary: Uranus, Neptune, and Pluto.

title: Grand Cross
summary: A powerful aspect pattern with four planets forming two oppositions and four squares, creating a cross shape.

title: Grand Trine
summary: Three planets forming trines to each other, indicating natural gifts.

title: Horary Astrology
summary: A branch of astrology that answers specific questions by casting a chart for the moment the question is asked.

title: Horary Astrology
summary: A branch of astrology that answers specific questions by casting a chart for the moment the question is asked.

title: Horoscope
summary: Originally referring to the Ascendant or rising sign, the term now commonly means astrological forecasts based on Sun sign positions.

title: House
summary: One of twelve divisions of the birth chart, each representing a different area of life.

title: House System
summary: The method used to divide the chart into 12 houses.

title: IC
summary: The Imum Coeli or "bottom of the sky.

title: Imum Coeli
summary: The IC or "Bottom of the Sky" - the lowest point of the chart opposite the Midheaven.

title: Ingress
summary: When a planet enters a new zodiac sign.

title: Intercepted Sign
summary: A sign fully contained within a house, not appearing on any house cusp.

title: Jupiter
summary: The planet of expansion, luck, and wisdom.

title: Lilith
summary: Black Moon Lilith represents the lunar apogee—the Moon's farthest point from Earth.

title: Lot of Fortune
summary: An Arabic Part calculated from the Ascendant, Sun, and Moon.

title: Luminary
summary: The Sun and Moon, the two brightest celestial bodies.

title: Lunar Eclipse
summary: A Full Moon that occurs near the lunar nodes, with Earth's shadow on the Moon.

title: Lunar Nodes
summary: The North and South Nodes describe your growth direction and past patterns across the chart.

title: Malefic Planets
summary: Mars and Saturn - planets that bring challenges that strengthen character.

title: Mars
summary: The planet of action, desire, and assertion.

title: Mercury
summary: The planet of communication, thinking, and information processing.

title: Midheaven
summary: The highest point in the chart representing career, public image, and life direction.

title: Modality
summary: The three qualities (Cardinal, Fixed, Mutable) describing how signs express energy.

title: Moon
summary: Your emotional nature, instincts, and subconscious patterns.

title: Moon Sign
summary: The zodiac sign the Moon was in at your birth, governing your emotional nature and instincts.

title: Mundane Astrology
summary: The branch of astrology dealing with world events, nations, and collective phenomena.

title: Mutable Signs
summary: Signs at the end of each season - adaptable, flexible, and embrace transition.

title: Natal Chart
summary: A map of the sky at the exact moment and location of your birth, showing planetary positions.

title: Neptune
summary: The planet of dreams, spirituality, and dissolution.

title: North Node
summary: Your soul's evolutionary direction and lessons to embrace in this lifetime.

title: Opposition
summary: An aspect of 180° between planets, creating tension and requiring balance.

title: Orb
summary: The degree of allowance when calculating aspects - tighter orbs are stronger.

title: Outer Planets
summary: Uranus, Neptune, and Pluto.

title: Part of Fortune
summary: An Arabic Part calculated from Sun, Moon, and Ascendant positions.

title: Personal Planets
summary: The Sun, Moon, Mercury, Venus, and Mars.

title: Placidus
summary: The most commonly used house system in Western astrology.

title: Planetary Ruler
summary: Each zodiac sign is governed by a planet that shares its essential nature.

title: Pluto
summary: The planet of transformation, power, and rebirth.

title: Polarity
summary: The division of signs into Masculine (Fire/Air) and Feminine (Earth/Water), also called Yang and Yin or Positive and Negative.

title: Progression
summary: A forecasting technique where one day after birth equals one year of life.

title: Retrograde
summary: When a planet appears to move backward, a time for review and reflection.

title: Rising Sign
summary: Another name for the Ascendant. The zodiac sign ascending on the eastern horizon at birth.

title: Rulership
summary: The relationship between a planet and the sign(s) it governs.

title: Saturn
summary: The planet of structure, discipline, and karma.

title: Saturn Return
summary: When Saturn returns to its natal position around age 29-30, marking major life transition.

title: Separating Aspect
summary: When a faster planet is moving away from exact aspect with a slower planet.

title: Sextile
summary: A harmonious aspect of 60° representing opportunities that require effort to activate.

title: Sidereal Zodiac
summary: A zodiac aligned with actual star constellations, used in Vedic astrology.

title: Social Planets
summary: Jupiter and Saturn.

title: Solar Arc
summary: A progression technique where all planets move forward at the same rate as the progressed Sun (about 1° per year).

title: Solar Eclipse
summary: A New Moon that occurs near the lunar nodes, blocking the Sun's light.

title: Solar Return
summary: A chart for the exact moment the Sun returns to its natal position each year.

title: South Node
summary: Past life gifts, comfort zones, and patterns to release.

title: Square
summary: A challenging aspect of 90° creating friction that drives growth.

title: Station
summary: The moment when a planet appears to stand still before changing direction (stationing retrograde or stationing direct).

title: Stellium
summary: Three or more planets in the same sign or house, intensifying that area of life.

title: Succedent House
summary: The 2nd, 5th, 8th, and 11th houses.

title: Sun
summary: The core of your identity, ego, and life purpose.

title: Sun Sign
summary: The zodiac sign the Sun was in at your birth, representing your core identity and life purpose.

title: Synastry
summary: The comparison of two birth charts to analyze relationship compatibility.

title: T-Square
summary: Two planets in opposition both square to a third, creating dynamic tension.

title: Transit
summary: The current movement of planets through the zodiac and their aspects to your natal chart.

title: Transpersonal Planets
summary: Another name for the outer planets (Uranus, Neptune, Pluto).

title: Trine
summary: A harmonious aspect of 120° indicating natural talent and ease.

title: Tropical Zodiac
summary: The zodiac used in Western astrology, based on the seasons.

title: Uranus
summary: The planet of revolution, innovation, and sudden change.

title: Vedic Astrology
summary: Also called Jyotish, the traditional Hindu system of astrology.

title: Venus
summary: The planet of love, beauty, pleasure, and values.

title: Vertex
summary: A mathematical point often called the "fated encounter" point.

title: Void of Course Moon
summary: When the Moon makes no major aspects before leaving its current sign.

title: Water Signs
summary: Cancer, Scorpio, and Pisces.

title: Whole Sign Houses
summary: The oldest house system, where each sign equals one house.

title: Zodiac
summary: A belt of the heavens divided into twelve equal signs (Aries through Pisces), each spanning 30 degrees.

title: Aquarius
summary: Aquarius is the eleventh sign of the zodiac, a fixed air sign ruled by Uranus. Known for innovation, independence, and humanitarian ideals.

title: Aries
summary: Aries is the first sign of the zodiac, a cardinal fire sign ruled by Mars. Known for courage, initiative, and pioneering spirit.

title: Cancer
summary: Cancer is the fourth sign of the zodiac, a cardinal water sign ruled by the Moon. Known for nurturing, emotional depth, and strong family bonds.

title: Capricorn
summary: Capricorn is the tenth sign of the zodiac, a cardinal earth sign ruled by Saturn. Known for ambition, discipline, and responsibility.

title: Gemini
summary: Gemini is the third sign of the zodiac, a mutable air sign ruled by Mercury. Known for curiosity, communication, and adaptability.

title: Leo
summary: Leo is the fifth sign of the zodiac, a fixed fire sign ruled by the Sun. Known for creativity, confidence, and natural leadership.

title: Libra
summary: Libra is the seventh sign of the zodiac, a cardinal air sign ruled by Venus. Known for seeking balance, harmony, and partnership.

title: Pisces
summary: Pisces is the twelfth sign of the zodiac, a mutable water sign ruled by Neptune. Known for intuition, compassion, and spiritual depth.

title: Sagittarius
summary: Sagittarius is the ninth sign of the zodiac, a mutable fire sign ruled by Jupiter. Known for adventure, philosophy, and optimism.

title: Scorpio
summary: Scorpio is the eighth sign of the zodiac, a fixed water sign ruled by Pluto. Known for intensity, transformation, and emotional depth.

title: Taurus
summary: Taurus is the second sign of the zodiac, a fixed earth sign ruled by Venus. Known for stability, sensuality, and appreciation of beauty.

title: Virgo
summary: Virgo is the sixth sign of the zodiac, a mutable earth sign ruled by Mercury. Known for analytical thinking, attention to detail, and service.
